  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 2cbaeec8dbe84e069925173ac3a6210b, type: 3}
  m_Name: Dlg_Tutorial_Opening
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ElementalAlchemist.Dialogue.DialogueData
  _speaker: Grand Master
  _lines:
  - Ah, you're awake. Ready for your training?
  - Did you forget? Today we start your journey into the alchemy world.
  - "Once we're done, you'll be just like me \u2014 a Grand Master."
  - Unfortunately alchemy forbids human transmutation, so you'll remain that short.
    But at least in rank you'll feel big.
  - "Now \u2014 alchemy is the art of fusing different elements into new ones."
  - We can't create something from nothing. We transmute what we have into what we
    want.
  - And for that, you first need to learn the elements.
  - There are four core elements, and you'll always need them in your lab. So let's
    get yours properly set up.
  - First, water. Head to the river and fetch some.
